{"id":965,"date":"2009-11-09T07:00:18","date_gmt":"2009-11-09T13:00:18","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/architectural_identity_for_applied_sciences_university.php"},"modified":"2009-11-09T07:00:18","modified_gmt":"2009-11-09T13:00:18","slug":"architectural_identity_for_applied_sciences_university","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/architectural_identity_for_applied_sciences_university.php","title":{"rendered":"Architectural Identity for Applied Sciences University"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/nhl_uni_logo.gif\" alt=\"NHL University, Before and After Logo\" \/>\n<p>Starting with the 2009\/2010 school year, the Northern Hogeschool Leeuwarden in The Netherlands &mdash; a 10,000-student, medium-sized university specializing in applied sciences &mdash; will be known as <a href=\"http:\/\/www.nhl.nl\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">NHL University<\/a>, and will soon be occupying a new, fancy and diagonally-inclined building designed by Dutch architect <a href=\"http:\/\/www.ahh.nl\">Herman Hertzberger<\/a>. For the university&#8217;s new era, Amsterdam based <a href=\"http:\/\/www.koeweidenpostma.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">koeweiden postma<\/a> designed a new identity inspired by the building.<\/p><!--more--><p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/nhl_uni_building.jpg\" alt=\"NHL University\" \/><\/p>\n<p class=\"caption\">New campus designed by <a href=\"http:\/\/www.ahh.nl\">Herman Hertzberger<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/nhl_uni_logo_lock-ups.gif\" alt=\"NHL University\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Luckily, the new identity doesn&#8217;t just show a reduced, black and white version of the building, but instead it takes its cues from the building&#8217;s lines and structure, all fairly evident in the sturdy and dynamic NHL acronym, which comes in two orientations. I wonder if five, seven or fifteen different perspectives of the acronym would have been more interesting, or just overkill? Maybe a little of both. The identity then expands in its applications by offering a wide range of colors as well as a <em>very<\/em> interesting family of typefaces that I would have probably never put together myself but look fairly convincing once applied. And to add a little visual excitement, there is a grid from which semi-random shapes can be constructed and used as holding forms or just background patterns. The overall effect is a nice combination of serious and playful, helping NHL University feel like a twenty-first century institution.<\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/nhl_uni_id_elements.gif\" alt=\"NHL University\" \/><\/p>\n<p class=\"caption\">Identity elements: a family of colors, typefaces and angled shapes (based on the diagonal lines of the building).<\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/nhl_uni_applications_01.jpg\" alt=\"NHL University\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/nhl_uni_applications_02.jpg\" alt=\"NHL University\" \/><\/p>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<script type=\"text\/javascript\" src=\"swfobject.js\"><\/script>\n<script type=\"text\/javascript\">\n\t<!--\n\tfunction pollSystemObj()\n\t{\n\t\tvar now = new Date();\n\t\tvar hour = now.getHours();\n\t\tvar minute = now.getMinutes();\n\t\tvar second = now.getSeconds();\n\t\tvar timeString = hour +\t'_' + minute + '_' + second;\n\t\t\/\/ create player swf object\n\t\t\/\/ <![CDATA[\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_20091109_config_01.xml&#038;xyz=poll_20091109_votes_01.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"282\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv1\");\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_20091109_config_02.xml